f (result == null) {\\n            try {\\n                @SuppressWarnings(\\\"unchecked\\\")\\n                Class<WebSocketContainer> clazz =\\n                        (Class<WebSocketContainer>) Class.forName(DEFAULT_PROVIDER_CLASS_NAME);\\n                result = clazz.getConstructor().newInstance();\\n            } catch (ReflectiveOperationException | IllegalArgumentException | SecurityException e) {\\n                // No options left. Just return null.\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return result;\\n    }\\n\\n    protected abstract WebSocketContainer getContainer();\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777394337030}]}\n1649:[thinking] I see that the status shows the metadata directory as untracked, which makes me think maybe the file exists, but Git isn't recognizing it. I might need to check the full status to determine if the repository is empty. I shouldn't touch anything unrelated, but I want to commit only our new test. I need to see the Git status to clarify what’s going on with the metadata directory.\n1655:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Investigating Git status**\\n\\nI see that the status shows the metadata directory as untracked, which makes me think maybe the file exists, but Git isn't recognizing it. I might need to check the full status to determine if the repository is empty. I shouldn't touch anything unrelated, but I want to commit only our new test. I need to see the Git status to clarify what’s going on with the metadata directory.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0d9e4620c2abed660169f0e2d74dd081919604365af637e508\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8OLZ4AxhYZ9xjRqB6hBBFiWoZOw67m91p_vlR0uQ6EYq5ynQJYSvXq_LWIPmua2gnklSJUanvci-3mRPKLSIptHMHK7oTrbLgU5eoR5mQHo9s84L3JDKqxMLKZ3XEDg1_1bdnKDTFIJW1iOcOx7QuNmbwUNdzsP1fL5DqTjRu1LdIzZhn9l8f1OFKsAjmd-Us7DFWOWOv4zrEHiKeGEDFigMJ6H3uA