\"totalTokens\": 21995, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777394352190, \"responseId\": \"resp_0d9e4620c2abed660169f0e2b09604819180f3833df7ba77e9\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_DB0tSbh43UHA0JF5swDygmYY|fc_0d9e4620c2abed660169f0e2b37f908191b61ec58f75470228\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more\\n * contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with\\n * this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.\\n * The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0\\n * (the \\\"License\\\"); you may not use this file except in compliance with\\n * the License.  You may obtain a copy of the License at\\n *\\n *     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\\n *\\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \\\"AS IS\\\" BASIS,\\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\\n * limitations under the License.\\n */\\npackage org.apache.tomcat.websocket;\\n\\nimport javax.websocket.ContainerProvider;\\nimport javax.websocket.WebSocketContainer;\\n\\n@aQute.bnd.annotation.spi.ServiceProvider(value = ContainerProvider.class)\\npublic class WsContainerProvider extends ContainerProvider {\\n\\n    @Override\\n    protected WebSocketContainer getContainer() {\\n        return new WsWebSocketContainer();\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777394355918}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T16-40-17-721982Z.log:1309:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 0, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777394355922}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T16-40-17-721982Z.log:1323:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating ServiceLoader behavior**\\n\\nI'm contemplating how ServiceLoader interacts with providers: it won't fallback if it finds one. To trigger a fallback, I need ServiceLoader not to find any providers, possibly by tweaking the thread context classloader. When I use ServiceLoader.load(ContainerProvider.class), it relies on the TCCL to load resources. If I set the TCCL to an empty URLClassLoader with no parent, that should ideally yield null, activating the fallback mechanism I need. However, I'll need to ensure the service loading works as intended within that context.\\n\\n**Exploring native image issues**\\n\\nI'm being cautious about creating a URLClassLoader for a native image. While it might work in the JVM, dynamic class loading can be tricky in a native context, especially since an empty URLClassLoader has no URLs. To manage resources, I’ll set the TCCL to a custom ClassLoader that overrides the getResources method to return an empty result. I’ll ensure that the fallback mechanism for loading the ContainerProvider works properly by reflecting on the WsWebSocketContainer and making sure the necessary metadata for reflection is included.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0d9e4620c2abed660169f0e2b6e0f88191adecd3985da7a7fb\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8OK_ClMeojTkxHa4xPaxLil